{"name": "graphql-server-core", "metadata": {"name": "graphql-server-core", "version": "2.0.0", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: PyPy", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries"], "home_page": "https://github.com/graphql-python/graphql-server-core", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "GraphQL Server tools for powering your server", "upload_time": 1584466557}, "documentation": ["# GraphQL-Server-Core\n\n[![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/graphql-server-core.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/graphql-server-core)\n[![Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/graphql-python/graphql-server-core.svg?branch=master)](https://travis-ci.org/graphql-python/graphql-server-core)\n[![Coverage Status](https://codecov.io/gh/graphql-python/graphql-server-core/branch/master/graph/badge.svg)](https://codecov.io/gh/graphql-python/graphql-server-core)\n\nGraphQL-Server-Core is a base library that serves as a helper\nfor building GraphQL servers or integrations into existing web frameworks using\n[GraphQL-Core](https://github.com/graphql-python/graphql-core).\n\n## Existing integrations built with GraphQL-Server-Core\n\n| Server integration | Package |\n|---|---|\n| Flask | [flask-graphql](https://github.com/graphql-python/flask-graphql/) |\n| Sanic |[sanic-graphql](https://github.com/graphql-python/sanic-graphql/) |\n| AIOHTTP | [aiohttp-graphql](https://github.com/graphql-python/aiohttp-graphql) |\n| WebOb (Pyramid, TurboGears) |  [webob-graphql](https://github.com/graphql-python/webob-graphql/) |\n| WSGI | [wsgi-graphql](https://github.com/moritzmhmk/wsgi-graphql) |\n| Responder | [responder.ext.graphql](https://github.com/kennethreitz/responder/blob/master/responder/ext/graphql.py) |\n\n## Other integrations using GraphQL-Core or Graphene\n\n| Server integration | Package |\n|---|---|\n| Django | [graphene-django](https://github.com/graphql-python/graphene-django/) |\n\n## Documentation\n\nThe `graphql_server` package provides these public helper functions:\n\n * `run_http_query`\n * `encode_execution_results`\n * `load_json_body`\n * `json_encode`\n * `json_encode_pretty`\n\nAll functions in the package are annotated with type hints and docstrings,\nand you can build HTML documentation from these using `bin/build_docs`.\n\nYou can also use one of the existing integrations listed above as\nblueprint to build your own integration or GraphQL server implementations.\n\nPlease let us know when you have built something new, so we can list it here.\n\n## Contributing\nSee [CONTRIBUTING.md](CONTRIBUTING.md)"], "modules": [{"name": "graphql_server.error", "documentation": ["Error classes provided by graphql_server"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "graphql_server.error.HttpQueryError", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [{"name": "graphql_server.error.HttpQueryError.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "status_code", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "message", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "is_graphql_error", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "headers", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Create a HTTP query error.\n\nYou need to pass the HTTP status code, the message that shall be shown,\nwhether this is a GraphQL error, and the HTTP headers that shall be sent."]}, {"name": "graphql_server.error.HttpQueryError.__eq__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "other", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Check whether this HTTP query error is equal to another one."]}, {"name": "graphql_server.error.HttpQueryError.__hash__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Create a hash value for this HTTP query error."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["The error class for HTTP errors produced by running GraphQL queries."]}], "exports": [{"name": "graphql_server.error.HttpQueryError", "xref": {"fqname": "graphql_server.error.HttpQueryError", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "setup", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "setup.install_requires", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.tests_requires", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.dev_requires", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "tests.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "tests.utils.as_dicts", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "results", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Convert execution results to a list of tuples of dicts for better comparison."]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "tests.conftest", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "tests.conftest.collect_ignore_glob", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "tests.test_error", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "tests.test_error.test_create_http_query_error", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_error.test_compare_http_query_errors", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_error.test_hash_http_query_errors", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "tests", "documentation": ["GraphQL-Server-Core Tests"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "graphql_server", "documentation": ["GraphQL-Server-Core\n===================\n\nGraphQL-Server-Core is a base library that serves as a helper\nfor building GraphQL servers or integrations into existing web frameworks using\n[GraphQL-Core](https://github.com/graphql-python/graphql-core)."], "functions": [{"name": "graphql_server.run_http_query", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "schema", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "request_method", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "query_data", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "batch_enabled", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "catch", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**execute_options", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Execute GraphQL coming from an HTTP query against a given schema.\n\nYou need to pass the schema (that is supposed to be already validated),\nthe request_method (that must be either \"get\" or \"post\"),\nthe data from the HTTP request body, and the data from the query string.\nBy default, only one parameter set is expected, but if you set batch_enabled,\nyou can pass data that contains a list of parameter sets to run multiple\nqueries as a batch execution using a single HTTP request. You can specify\nwhether results returning HTTPQueryErrors should be caught and skipped.\nAll other keyword arguments are passed on to the GraphQL-Core function for\nexecuting GraphQL queries.\n\nReturns a ServerResults tuple with the list of ExecutionResults as first item\nand the list of parameters that have been used for execution as second item.", "The public helper functions"]}, {"name": "graphql_server.encode_execution_results", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "execution_results", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "format_error", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "is_batch", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "encode", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Serialize the ExecutionResults.\n\nThis function takes the ExecutionResults that are returned by run_http_query()\nand serializes them using JSON to produce an HTTP response.\nIf you set is_batch=True, then all ExecutionResults will be returned, otherwise only\nthe first one will be used. You can also pass a custom function that formats the\nerrors in the ExecutionResults, expecting a dictionary as result and another custom\nfunction that is used to serialize the output.\n\nReturns a ServerResponse tuple with the serialized response as the first item and\na status code of 200 or 400 in case any result was invalid as the second item."]}, {"name": "graphql_server.load_json_body", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Load the request body as a dictionary or a list.\n\nThe body must be passed in a string and will be deserialized from JSON,\nraising an HttpQueryError in case of invalid JSON."]}, {"name": "graphql_server.json_encode", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "pretty", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Serialize the given data(a dictionary or a list) using JSON.\n\nThe given data (a dictionary or a list) will be serialized using JSON\nand returned as a string that will be nicely formatted if you set pretty=True."]}, {"name": "graphql_server.json_encode_pretty", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Serialize the given data using JSON with nice formatting."]}, {"name": "graphql_server.get_graphql_params", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "query_data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Fetch GraphQL query, variables and operation name parameters from given data.\n\nYou need to pass both the data from the HTTP request body and the HTTP query string.\nParams from the request body will take precedence over those from the query string.\n\nYou will get a RequestParams tuple with these parameters in return."]}, {"name": "graphql_server.load_json_variables", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "variables", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return the given GraphQL variables as a dictionary.\n\nThe function returns the given GraphQL variables, making sure they are\ndeserialized from JSON to a dictionary first if necessary. In case of\ninvalid JSON input, an HttpQueryError will be raised."]}, {"name": "graphql_server.execute_graphql_request", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "schema", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "params", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "allow_only_query", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "backend", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Execute a GraphQL request and return an ExecutionResult.\n\nYou need to pass the GraphQL schema and the GraphQLParams that you can get\nwith the get_graphql_params() function. If you only want to allow GraphQL query\noperations, then set allow_only_query=True. You can also specify a custom\nGraphQLBackend instance that shall be used by GraphQL-Core instead of the\ndefault one. All other keyword arguments are passed on to the GraphQL-Core\nfunction for executing GraphQL queries."]}, {"name": "graphql_server.execute_graphql_request_as_promise", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "graphql_server.get_response", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "schema", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "params", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "catch_exc", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "allow_only_query", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Get an individual execution result as response, with option to catch errors.\n\nThis does the same as execute_graphql_request() except that you can catch errors\nthat belong to an exception class that you need to pass as a parameter."]}, {"name": "graphql_server.format_execution_result", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "execution_result", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "format_error", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Format an execution result into a GraphQLResponse.\n\nThis converts the given execution result into a FormattedResult that contains\nthe ExecutionResult converted to a dictionary and an appropriate status code."]}], "variables": [{"name": "graphql_server.RequestParams", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "graphql_server.ServerResults", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "graphql_server.ServerResponse", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "graphql_server.FormattedResult", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "graphql_server._NoException", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Private exception used when we don't want to catch any real exception."]}], "exports": [{"name": "graphql_server.encode_execution_results", "xref": {"fqname": "graphql_server.encode_execution_results", "project": null}}, {"name": "graphql_server.HttpQueryError", "xref": {"fqname": "graphql_server.error.HttpQueryError", "project": null}}, {"name": "graphql_server.json_encode", "xref": {"fqname": "graphql_server.json_encode", "project": null}}, {"name": "graphql_server.json_encode_pre